T3  - Mm '25
AB  - Today, truly immersive multimedia systems demand the integration of emerging multi-sensorial media, which go beyond traditional audiovisual signals to include haptics, olfaction, motion capture, electroencephalograms, and other novel media forms. To effectively incorporate these modalities into cutting-edge multimedia systems, advances are needed across the entire pipeline, from processing and encoding to seamless integration. In addition, human-centric factors such as ergonomics and user experience must be considered to ensure practical implementation. Our workshop, the International Workshop on Multi-Sensorial Media and Applications (MSMA'2025), seeks to attract contributions related to multi-sensorial media systems, including system design, evaluation, coding, delivery, media analysis, multi-modal interaction, human factors, ergonomics, and related areas. By fostering collaboration among researchers, MSMA aims to bridge existing work in the field, spark innovation, and push the boundaries of multimedia technology.
